rComments: Dr. Thomas is a good teacher. He will make you work for an "A". He will make you get something out of the class to apply to your everyday life.
This is a good class.  You have to read to get an "A."  Luckily, the readings are interesting.
This is a good class, he makes you think.  However, I wish that the lectures focused more on the readings.

Dr. Thomas (Don't call him Damion!) seems well educated but don't let the buttoned down white shirt fool you - he makes no sense! All of his material is made up from his own ideas with no backbone. He is very unorganized and has no structure to his material. I would not recommend taking his class!

I took Dr. Thomas' "Black Masculinity and Basketball " course.  This was the best class that I've taken at U of I.  He is very smart, engaging, and responsive to the needs of students.  Take this class if you can.
